abstract: “I I I I I I I I I I I I I I I hhhave absolutely no idea what Biden is talking about,” Ms. Sanders tweeted during the Democratic presidential debate. She later deleted the post and apologized.
snippet: “I I I I I I I I I I I I I I I hhhave absolutely no idea what Biden is talking about,” Ms. Sanders tweeted during the Democratic presidential debate. She later deleted the post and apologized.
lead_paragraph: Sarah Huckabee Sanders apologized late Thursday after she mocked comments by former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. during the Democratic presidential debate in which he recounted mentoring a boy who had a speech impediment.

abstract: Several factors unrelated to the facts are shielding President Trump in ways Nixon would have envied.
snippet: Several factors unrelated to the facts are shielding President Trump in ways Nixon would have envied.
lead_paragraph: Richard Nixon was a crafty president, at war with his political enemies but inclined to carry out most of his battles behind the scenes. Donald Trump trumpets his grievances, using public lashings to diminish his enemies and nip at allies who anger him. Nixon began his second term in January of 1973 with support from nearly 70 percent of the American people. Mr. Trump’s public approval has never hit 50 percent, according to the Gallup poll. Nixon saw his support steadily erode as details of the Watergate scandal trickled out. Mr. Trump’s support has held steady despite a fire hose of accusations. His approval rating stood at a typical 43 percent when the House opened its impeachment inquiry on Sept. 24.

abstract: It’s all about the states. A big question is how a plan could work in all of them.
snippet: It’s all about the states. A big question is how a plan could work in all of them.
lead_paragraph: Democratic presidential candidates are fighting over who should be eligible for free college based on income, but a bigger question is how to structure a plan that could work in all 50 states.
